---
import Button from '../../Button.astro'
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-slate-50">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 text-center">
      Who's building Storehouse.
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-10 items-start">
      <!-- Photo placeholder -->
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 mx-auto md:mx-0">
        <div class="w-40 h-40 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-storehouse-200 to-emerald-200 flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden">
          <span class="font-display text-4xl text-storehouse-700">RH</span>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-center text-sm text-slate-500">Randy Harmon</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Bio content -->
      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          I've spent 20+ years in real estate -- as an agent, a sales manager, and a broker. I watched Bob's lesson play out hundreds of times. Families who left margin thrived. Families who maxed out every dollar struggled the moment anything shifted.
        </p>

        <p>
          That pattern stuck with me because I'm living it too. I'm a husband and a dad, and our family runs on the same hierarchy Storehouse is built around: give first, save second, spend what remains. It's not a formula I invented. It's what the Bible teaches about money, and it works.
        </p>

        <p>
          Storehouse is one expression of that conviction. I'm also building
          <span class="text-slate-700 font-medium">The Candid Agent</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400"> -- honest real estate guidance</span> -- and
          <span class="text-slate-700 font-medium">Good News Garden</span>
          <span class="text-slate-400"> -- faith, family, and flourishing</span>.
          Different projects, same root: margin over maximum. Stewardship over consumption.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Sign off -->
    <div class="mt-12 text-center">
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-700 italic">
        Thanks for being here.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-slate-600">
        â€” Randy
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- CTAs -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
      <Button href="/waitlist" variant="primary" size="lg">
        Join the Waitlist
      </Button>
      <Button href="/philosophy" variant="secondary" size="lg">
        Read My Philosophy
      </Button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
